  "text": "Unlike dinucleon decay, n−n oscillation also requires flavor violation from R-parity conserving vertices. However, aside from the baryon violating A-term, all visible sector soft masses arise directly from gauge mediation, so their flavor structure comes entirely from Yukawa couplings. Thus, up to an overall coefficient, our n −n oscillation amplitudes are identical to those computed in [CITATION_1] . Chirality-preserving flavor-violating masses arise predominantly from MSSM F -terms after SUSY and electroweak symmetry breaking through e C Figure 9 . Dinucleon decay via baryonic RPV interactions. In the text we assume gluino exchange (left) dominates.",
